<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-11-13T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-11-13T08:00:00-05:00" n="317" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d317">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.114 Norway/17: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Biddle</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Oslo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-11-13T14:00:00+01:00">November
                                    13, 1935—2 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received November 14—4:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>25. Department’s telegram No. 16, November 12, 4 p.m. Note in <hi rend="italic">Anders</hi> case, which was sent the Minister of
                            Foreign Affairs July 18, was followed October 17 by oral request for
                            expedition of reply, supplemented by memorandum same date. Oral
                            representations and note regarding <hi rend="italic">Anders, Trajan</hi>
                            and <hi rend="italic">Reidun</hi> cases made at the Foreign Office
                            today. It has today been ascertained from appropriate official that <hi rend="italic">Anders</hi> case has been referred by the Ministry of
                            Commerce to the Minister of Justice; that judicial investigation is now
                            being made and that pertinent note will be sent very shortly to the
                            Legation. Despatch follows.<note n="72" xml:id="d317fn72">Despatch No.
                                38, November 16, not printed.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Biddle</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>